1
00:01:57,840 --> 00:02:02,200
The stars in the summer night

2
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:06,099
Quietly watching the two of them

3
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:07,120
What do you think?

4
00:02:07,200 --> 00:02:08,080
Have you heard this song before?

5
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:09,159
Sounds a bit familiar.

6
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:10,680
I think I've heard my grandpa hum it.

7
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:13,159
Pretty retro.

8
00:02:13,199 --> 00:02:13,759
Yusheng.

9
00:02:14,199 --> 00:02:15,400
Tell the truth.

10
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:17,120
Which generation are you actually from?

11
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:20,599
I saw this in Elder Cao's diary.

12
00:02:20,599 --> 00:02:21,280
Elder Cao?

13
00:02:22,120 --> 00:02:23,159
Which Elder Cao?

14
00:02:23,199 --> 00:02:24,120
The one in the back,

15
00:02:24,360 --> 00:02:26,199
that new senior at Pine and Crane Residence.

16
00:02:26,199 --> 00:02:26,719
Right?

17
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:27,599
Smart.

18
00:02:28,560 --> 00:02:29,599
In his diary,

19
00:02:29,719 --> 00:02:31,280
You actually peeked at his diary?

20
00:02:31,280 --> 00:02:31,759
Yes.

21
00:02:32,599 --> 00:02:34,120
What do you mean "peeked"?

22
00:02:34,599 --> 00:02:36,319
Elder Cao showed it to me himself.

23
00:02:36,520 --> 00:02:38,120
He even told me the stories one by one.

24
00:02:38,919 --> 00:02:39,639
In there,

25
00:02:39,639 --> 00:02:41,560
did he talk about anything related to love?

26
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:42,560
Of course he did.

27
00:02:45,360 --> 00:02:45,800
Naturally,

28
00:02:46,599 --> 00:02:48,759
I went to study the changes in social history.

29
00:02:49,439 --> 00:02:50,800
Stop being serious. Tell us.

30
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:51,599
Tell us.

31
00:02:51,639 --> 00:02:52,639
Tell us.

32
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:54,000
Elder Cao said,

33
00:02:55,319 --> 00:02:57,680
back when he was pasting paper boxes at the neighborhood factory,

34
00:02:58,240 --> 00:03:00,520
he had a first love who went through hardships with him.

35
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:03,199
They even built furniture and were ready to get married,

36
00:03:03,479 --> 00:03:04,740
but the girl's parents didn't agree.

37
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:06,039
They forcibly tore the two apart.

38
00:03:07,080 --> 00:03:07,960
And then?

39
00:03:08,199 --> 00:03:09,599
Elder Cao went out of town,

40
00:03:09,759 --> 00:03:11,080
got married and had children.

41
00:03:11,800 --> 00:03:13,039
But he still couldn't forget

42
00:03:13,039 --> 00:03:14,360
this first love named Yingzi.

43
00:03:15,479 --> 00:03:16,280
Named what?

44
00:03:16,680 --> 00:03:17,599
Yingzi.

45
00:03:18,280 --> 00:03:19,719
Also called Xiaoying.

46
00:03:20,319 --> 00:03:21,520
Her full name is

47
00:03:21,560 --> 00:03:22,319
Cai Xiaoying.

48
00:03:23,159 --> 00:03:23,800
Wait a minute.

49
00:03:24,960 --> 00:03:26,120
Cai Xiaoying.

50
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:28,360
Why does that name sound so familiar?

51
00:03:28,800 --> 00:03:30,400
I think it sounds familiar too.

52
00:03:30,759 --> 00:03:32,560
Cai Xiaoying...

53
00:03:33,479 --> 00:03:35,680
Cai Xiaoying...

54
00:03:37,039 --> 00:03:38,879
Auntie Cai!

55
00:03:43,960 --> 00:03:44,680
Auntie Cai

56
00:03:45,120 --> 00:03:47,560
Where did you work before?

57
00:03:48,919 --> 00:03:50,199
I'm just an ordinary citizen.

58
00:03:50,400 --> 00:03:52,919
How could I work at some big government agency?

59
00:03:53,199 --> 00:03:54,439
I was at that...

60
00:03:54,639 --> 00:03:56,520
state-run grocery store.

61
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:00,800
Later, that Korean supermarket, Baikelong,

62
00:04:00,879 --> 00:04:01,919
put it out of business.

63
00:04:02,039 --> 00:04:03,639
Is that supermarket Korean?

64
00:04:04,400 --> 00:04:05,280
What about before that?

65
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,879
Did you go to the grocery store right after high school?

66
00:04:07,960 --> 00:04:08,400
Pfft.

67
00:04:08,599 --> 00:04:09,759
No way.

68
00:04:10,479 --> 00:04:12,199
I didn't graduate high school at all.

69
00:04:14,800 --> 00:04:15,800
If I say it,

70
00:04:16,079 --> 00:04:17,360
you can't laugh at Auntie Cai.

71
00:04:18,199 --> 00:04:19,639
I wasn't even eighteen,

72
00:04:19,639 --> 00:04:22,920
and I went to the neighborhood factory to paste paper boxes.

73
00:04:23,040 --> 00:04:25,319
Back then, pasting one box earned five cents.

74
00:04:25,319 --> 00:04:26,560
That matches.

75
00:04:26,800 --> 00:04:27,759
What do you mean?

76
00:04:27,879 --> 00:04:29,319
So you think I'm only good for pasting paper boxes?

77
00:04:29,439 --> 00:04:32,120
Let me tell you, every trade produces a master.

78
00:04:32,319 --> 00:04:34,199
Just because I pasted boxes so well,

79
00:04:34,319 --> 00:04:37,079
I was exceptionally promoted to the grocery store.

80
00:04:37,079 --> 00:04:37,839
Auntie Cai,

81
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:40,160
when you were at this factory,

82
00:04:40,160 --> 00:04:42,160
did anything happen?

83
00:04:42,279 --> 00:04:43,519
What could happen?

84
00:04:43,519 --> 00:04:44,639
Just pasting paper boxes.

85
00:04:44,720 --> 00:04:46,240
Besides pasting paper boxes?

86
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:48,839
Did nothing else happen?

87
00:04:49,399 --> 00:04:51,319
Sometimes I'd help them fold pages too.

88
00:04:52,959 --> 00:04:53,600
Auntie Cai,

89
00:04:53,959 --> 00:04:55,680
when you were at this factory,

90
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:58,959
was there a young technician

91
00:04:59,199 --> 00:05:01,040
named Cao Dongfang?

92
00:05:01,199 --> 00:05:01,879
Yes, back...

93
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:06,839
How do you know that?

94
00:05:07,439 --> 00:05:08,600
Who told you?

95
00:05:11,519 --> 00:05:12,839
What did I come here for?

96
00:05:13,199 --> 00:05:14,000
It was me who wanted to see...

97
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,519
Has that community leader arrived?

98
00:05:16,000 --> 00:05:16,879
We...

99
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:18,800
really want to hear you recall again

100
00:05:18,800 --> 00:05:19,959
back at the neighborhood factory,

101
00:05:19,959 --> 00:05:20,920
the part about pasting paper boxes.

102
00:05:22,319 --> 00:05:24,399
What is it? Who is it, anyway?

103
00:05:24,480 --> 00:05:25,680
So mysterious.

104
00:05:25,759 --> 00:05:27,120
A grandpa.

105
00:05:29,759 --> 00:05:31,519
All that hype and it's just an old man.

106
00:05:31,680 --> 00:05:32,600
You know, around here,

107
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:35,000
besides old ladies, aren't they all old men?

108
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:40,360
Back then, I made a small technical innovation...

109
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:41,720
Grandpa...

110
00:05:41,800 --> 00:05:43,600
Let's not talk about that technical invention.

111
00:05:43,759 --> 00:05:46,000
Let's talk about you and that Xiaoying.

112
00:05:46,199 --> 00:05:47,199
Right, do you still remember?

113
00:05:47,199 --> 00:05:48,139
Of course.

114
00:05:48,139 --> 00:05:50,160
How could I not remember Xiaoying?

115
00:05:50,519 --> 00:05:52,920
If she appeared in front of you right now,

116
00:05:53,079 --> 00:05:54,319
would you still recognize her?

117
00:05:54,360 --> 00:05:55,360
Of course.

118
00:05:55,360 --> 00:05:57,560
How could I not recognize Xiaoying?

119
00:05:58,040 --> 00:05:58,839
Then look,

120
00:05:59,199 --> 00:06:00,240
who is this?

121
00:06:06,399 --> 00:06:07,439
You...

122
00:06:08,560 --> 00:06:10,439
You are...

123
00:06:10,439 --> 00:06:11,319
You...

124
00:06:11,639 --> 00:06:12,439
You are...

125
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:15,439
You must be the community leader, right?

126
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:17,240
Hello.

127
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:19,439
You are...

128
00:06:21,160 --> 00:06:23,600
You are Cao Dongfang.

129
00:06:23,879 --> 00:06:25,560
Yes, I am Cao Dongfang.

130
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:27,360
As expected of a leader,

131
00:06:27,439 --> 00:06:29,759
you even know my name.

132
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:31,560
You...

133
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:35,560
You don't even recognize me?

134
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:37,600
You have to forgive my eyes.

135
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:39,360
My cataracts are getting worse,

136
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:40,920
and my memory is getting worse.

137
00:06:41,800 --> 00:06:43,120
Have we met before?

138
00:06:43,319 --> 00:06:44,600
I'm new here.

139
00:06:44,680 --> 00:06:45,519
Cao Dongfang.

140
00:06:47,360 --> 00:06:50,600
Look at me closely again.

141
00:06:57,199 --> 00:06:58,720
You didn't expect this, did you?

142
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:01,399
That Little Ying's appearance

143
00:07:01,959 --> 00:07:05,560
Would one day be so old you couldn't recognize her

144
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:07,920
Yingzi

145
00:07:12,439 --> 00:07:13,360
Little Ying

146
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:16,959
I really didn't expect we'd reunite in our old age

147
00:07:19,079 --> 00:07:20,040
All these years

148
00:07:20,319 --> 00:07:21,879
I have never forgotten you

149
00:07:22,560 --> 00:07:23,360
You...

150
00:07:24,279 --> 00:07:25,480
Do you miss me too?

151
00:07:25,839 --> 00:07:26,839
I miss you

152
00:07:26,879 --> 00:07:28,000
I hate you to death

153
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:29,759
Hate me for what?

154
00:07:30,240 --> 00:07:32,279
Hate that you abandoned me back then

155
00:07:32,279 --> 00:07:33,399
And disappeared without a trace

156
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:35,240
How can you blame me for that?

157
00:07:35,720 --> 00:07:36,360
That was clearly because

158
00:07:36,360 --> 00:07:38,399
Your family didn't agree to our marriage

159
00:07:38,639 --> 00:07:40,360
My mother went to propose

160
00:07:40,399 --> 00:07:41,279
And was driven out

161
00:07:41,839 --> 00:07:44,079
So you just flew far away on your own?

162
00:07:44,279 --> 00:07:45,879
At the time, I had made up my mind

163
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:47,240
To leave my home and career

164
00:07:47,319 --> 00:07:48,439
And elope with you

165
00:07:48,439 --> 00:07:49,040
Then...

166
00:07:49,600 --> 00:07:50,519
Then what happened?

167
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:52,600
My parents certainly wouldn't spare me

168
00:07:53,120 --> 00:07:54,240
That was truly...

169
00:07:54,360 --> 00:07:56,000
A leather whip dipped in cold water

170
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:57,800
Beating without mercy

171
00:07:58,600 --> 00:07:59,399
That wasn't my dad

172
00:07:59,399 --> 00:08:00,319
That was Song Laosan

173
00:08:02,040 --> 00:08:03,560
Then what happened after that?

174
00:08:03,879 --> 00:08:05,160
You didn't jump into the river, did you?

175
00:08:05,279 --> 00:08:06,279
Isn't that obvious?

176
00:08:06,279 --> 00:08:07,120
If I had jumped into the river

177
00:08:07,120 --> 00:08:08,720
Would I still be sitting here talking to you?

178
00:08:09,279 --> 00:08:10,519
Then what happened after that?

179
00:08:11,319 --> 00:08:12,720
After that...

180
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:15,519
My parents forced me to go on blind dates

181
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:18,160
An arranged marriage to the Chen family

182
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:20,480
Then what happened after *that*?

183
00:08:21,319 --> 00:08:23,040
After *that*...

184
00:08:23,079 --> 00:08:25,240
The raw rice was cooked into mush

185
00:08:27,279 --> 00:08:29,600
Got married and had a baby

186
00:08:29,839 --> 00:08:31,759
Elders above, little ones below

187
00:08:32,360 --> 00:08:34,240
Not enough to wear or eat

188
00:08:34,399 --> 00:08:36,440
And the child's father passed away early

189
00:08:36,919 --> 00:08:39,000
I've been a widow for years, never remarried

190
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:40,799
Who is to blame for all this?

191
00:08:41,240 --> 00:08:42,159
Blame you?

192
00:08:42,519 --> 00:08:43,279
Blame you

193
00:08:43,279 --> 00:08:45,980
It's all your fault

194
00:08:50,759 --> 00:08:51,679
Little Cai, what are you...

195
00:08:53,200 --> 00:08:54,080
Didn't see anything

196
00:08:54,360 --> 00:08:55,639
Didn't see... I didn't see anything at all

197
00:09:03,039 --> 00:09:04,519
Yingzi, let's not cry

198
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,200
Aren't we reunited in our old age now?

199
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:11,080
I'll make up for everything I owe you in this life

200
00:09:11,759 --> 00:09:13,519
What's the use of you coming back now?

201
00:09:13,799 --> 00:09:14,799
It's too late

202
00:09:14,799 --> 00:09:15,919
It's not too late

203
00:09:16,399 --> 00:09:18,039
You lost your spouse in middle age

204
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:19,320
I am single in my old age

205
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:21,919
That we could reunite in the nursing home

206
00:09:22,120 --> 00:09:23,440
Who knows if it isn't Heaven

207
00:09:23,440 --> 00:09:25,080
Giving us another chance?

208
00:09:37,320 --> 00:09:38,120
Xiao Cai

209
00:09:39,120 --> 00:09:41,399
Does Elder Cao want to...

210
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:43,639
...rekindle his romance with you?

211
00:09:45,840 --> 00:09:46,960
Yeah, Xiao Cai.

212
00:09:47,360 --> 00:09:48,960
Fate is rare.

213
00:09:49,039 --> 00:09:50,639
You really shouldn't miss this.

214
00:09:53,480 --> 00:09:54,480
He...

215
00:09:55,679 --> 00:09:58,000
He definitely has that intention.

216
00:09:58,679 --> 00:09:59,679
But...

217
00:10:00,039 --> 00:10:01,960
As a lady...

218
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:04,279
I can't be the one to bring it up first.

219
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:06,639
So I thought...

220
00:10:07,200 --> 00:10:09,639
I'd find a matchmaker to pass the word.

221
00:10:11,399 --> 00:10:13,320
Matchmaking is your specialty!

222
00:10:13,519 --> 00:10:15,039
Why trouble anyone else?

223
00:10:16,139 --> 00:10:17,320
What do you know?

224
00:10:17,759 --> 00:10:20,480
Who acts as their own matchmaker?

225
00:10:20,480 --> 00:10:21,080
True.

226
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:22,799
So I thought...

227
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:26,679
Mr. Li...

228
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:28,240
...could help me with this.

229
00:10:28,519 --> 00:10:29,000
Right.

230
00:10:29,519 --> 00:10:29,960
Good.

231
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:31,000
Perfect.

232
00:10:31,399 --> 00:10:32,240
It's appropriate.

233
00:10:32,840 --> 00:10:33,559
Me?

234
00:10:34,799 --> 00:10:36,000
You're joking.

235
00:10:36,519 --> 00:10:37,440
I can't do it.

236
00:10:37,440 --> 00:10:38,919
No way.

237
00:10:38,919 --> 00:10:40,519
Why not?

238
00:10:40,639 --> 00:10:41,919
A person only has one or...

239
00:10:41,919 --> 00:10:43,399
...two major events in a lifetime.

240
00:10:43,480 --> 00:10:44,919
We're just asking for a small favor.

241
00:10:44,919 --> 00:10:46,519
Look how troubled you're acting.

242
00:10:46,879 --> 00:10:48,279
It's not that I'm troubled.

243
00:10:48,399 --> 00:10:48,919
It's just...

244
00:10:49,559 --> 00:10:51,120
I really don't know how.

245
00:10:51,159 --> 00:10:52,960
What's there not to know?

246
00:10:52,960 --> 00:10:53,519
I'll teach you.

247
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:56,080
First...

248
00:10:56,360 --> 00:10:58,600
We don't have "parents' orders."

249
00:10:58,799 --> 00:11:00,840
And no need for horoscopes.

250
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:03,279
We are compatible.

251
00:11:03,279 --> 00:11:04,360
We know each other inside out.

252
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:06,879
You just need to be the middleman and pass a word.

253
00:11:07,240 --> 00:11:08,200
That's it.

254
00:11:08,360 --> 00:11:10,120
Such a simple, wonderful thing.

255
00:11:11,679 --> 00:11:13,039
If we weren't such good friends...

256
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:16,000
I wouldn't assign this good deed to you.

257
00:11:16,960 --> 00:11:18,360
So I'm the one benefiting here?

258
00:11:18,960 --> 00:11:20,080
You...

259
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:21,080
Just don't refuse.

260
00:11:21,320 --> 00:11:22,480
I saw it long ago...

261
00:11:22,480 --> 00:11:24,679
You have the talent of a matchmaker or shaman.

262
00:11:24,679 --> 00:11:25,960
You're talking about a witch.

263
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:27,279
I'm talking about a matchmaker.

264
00:11:27,799 --> 00:11:28,840
Who's the matchmaker?

265
00:11:29,960 --> 00:11:30,919
Mr. Li here.

266
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:31,639
You...

267
00:11:31,639 --> 00:11:34,399
If you can help, just help.

268
00:11:34,519 --> 00:11:36,559
Consider it accumulating virtue...

269
00:11:36,600 --> 00:11:38,759
...and taking pleasure in helping others.

270
00:11:41,879 --> 00:11:42,519
Alright then.

271
00:11:43,799 --> 00:11:44,639
I'll take the trouble...

272
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:46,200
...and be a matchmaker this once.

273
00:11:46,799 --> 00:11:47,399
Okay.

274
00:11:47,840 --> 00:11:49,480
I'll go invite Elder Cao over right now.

275
00:11:57,759 --> 00:11:59,559
I bumped into my first love last year.

276
00:12:00,039 --> 00:12:00,840
To be honest...

277
00:12:00,840 --> 00:12:02,120
I was very disappointed.

278
00:12:02,399 --> 00:12:02,960
Really.

279
00:12:03,879 --> 00:12:06,120
The feeling from back then was completely gone.

280
00:12:06,919 --> 00:12:08,000
Is that so?

281
00:12:09,159 --> 00:12:11,080
Look at Xiao Cai and Elder Cao.

282
00:12:11,360 --> 00:12:13,159
They've been apart for over forty years.

283
00:12:13,159 --> 00:12:14,440
People are different.

284
00:12:15,039 --> 00:12:16,279
Some value love and loyalty.

285
00:12:16,320 --> 00:12:17,519
Others are heartless and fickle.

286
00:12:18,120 --> 00:12:18,799
Who are you pointing at?

287
00:12:19,440 --> 00:12:20,399
Distinguished elders...

288
