586
00:21:26,000 --> 00:21:26,759
that's going too far

587
00:21:26,759 --> 00:21:28,680
Don't make me laugh

588
00:21:28,759 --> 00:21:29,880
It's your family

589
00:21:29,880 --> 00:21:32,039
eyeing our family's apartments, isn't it?

590
00:21:32,640 --> 00:21:34,119
Ridiculous

591
00:21:34,119 --> 00:21:35,799
Look at your petty stuff

592
00:21:36,380 --> 00:21:38,000
Our family's apartments

593
00:21:39,119 --> 00:21:39,480
Look

594
00:21:40,480 --> 00:21:41,279
Stop arguing, all of you

595
00:21:47,880 --> 00:21:48,880
I've made up my mind.

596
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,599
All my antiques...

597
00:21:54,599 --> 00:21:55,519
And my savings...

598
00:21:56,880 --> 00:21:58,839
I'll give them all to you filial children.

599
00:21:59,160 --> 00:22:00,359
I knew it.

600
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:02,599
You have to give all these assets to us.

601
00:22:04,640 --> 00:22:05,240
Dad.

602
00:22:05,799 --> 00:22:08,880
Who did you say you're giving the property to?

603
00:22:09,960 --> 00:22:11,599
I've also made up my mind.

604
00:22:12,039 --> 00:22:14,039
I'll leave the house to you and Doudou, alright?

605
00:22:14,480 --> 00:22:15,519
Really?

606
00:22:15,980 --> 00:22:17,480
Oh my!

607
00:22:17,960 --> 00:22:19,079
Mom.

608
00:22:20,039 --> 00:22:22,519
You agreed to transfer the house title?

609
00:22:23,359 --> 00:22:25,319
Dad, you didn't misunderstand, right?

610
00:22:25,559 --> 00:22:27,480
I'm your little girl.

611
00:22:27,480 --> 00:22:28,440
As for me...

612
00:22:28,519 --> 00:22:30,799
I'm thinking entirely of you.

613
00:22:31,440 --> 00:22:32,900
Just like my younger siblings...

614
00:22:32,900 --> 00:22:34,480
We're all thinking the same thing.

615
00:22:35,079 --> 00:22:36,079
Sis.

616
00:22:36,759 --> 00:22:37,619
Tell me...

617
00:22:37,619 --> 00:22:39,960
How are we thinking exactly the same?

618
00:22:39,960 --> 00:22:40,640
That's right.

619
00:22:40,640 --> 00:22:42,759
What are we even fighting for?

620
00:22:42,759 --> 00:22:44,480
Isn't it all for the two elders?

621
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:46,400
Isn't that right, Dabao?

622
00:22:46,400 --> 00:22:47,279
That's right.

623
00:22:47,640 --> 00:22:50,839
I wish Mom the best from the bottom of my heart.

624
00:22:51,079 --> 00:22:51,720
And...

625
00:22:52,599 --> 00:22:54,160
Our dad.

626
00:22:55,640 --> 00:22:56,200
From now on...

627
00:22:56,440 --> 00:22:57,519
We are just one family.

628
00:22:57,920 --> 00:22:58,680
Right, son?

629
00:22:59,200 --> 00:22:59,720
Right.

630
00:23:00,079 --> 00:23:00,680
Grandpa.

631
00:23:01,000 --> 00:23:01,680
The two of you...

632
00:23:01,759 --> 00:23:03,160
A reunion spanning a century.

633
00:23:03,319 --> 00:23:04,359
This belated love...

634
00:23:04,519 --> 00:23:05,480
Is so precious.

635
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:06,920
Director Chang.

636
00:23:07,400 --> 00:23:08,960
We can't let the elders down.

637
00:23:09,119 --> 00:23:09,880
This wedding...

638
00:23:10,160 --> 00:23:11,839
Must be lively and grand.

639
00:23:12,059 --> 00:23:12,339
Right.

640
00:23:12,480 --> 00:23:13,160
Yes.

641
00:23:13,920 --> 00:23:14,599
Yingzi.

642
00:23:15,039 --> 00:23:16,519
After more than forty years...

643
00:23:17,119 --> 00:23:19,240
We are finally together.

644
00:23:20,920 --> 00:23:21,720
Brother Dongfang.

645
00:23:22,599 --> 00:23:24,160
We will never be apart again.

646
00:23:27,799 --> 00:23:28,920
Good.

647
00:23:30,039 --> 00:23:30,559
Good.

648
00:23:30,640 --> 00:23:32,160
Then I declare...

649
00:23:32,240 --> 00:23:34,359
Today's wedding ceremony is complete.

650
00:23:34,640 --> 00:23:37,559
Great!

651
00:23:37,559 --> 00:23:40,599
Next, let's send off the newlyweds...

652
00:23:40,720 --> 00:23:41,240
No, wait.

653
00:23:41,319 --> 00:23:43,279
The elderly couple to the bridal chamber.

654
00:23:43,279 --> 00:23:45,799
Great!

655
00:23:50,240 --> 00:23:51,480
I'm an old lady now.

656
00:23:52,039 --> 00:23:53,839
Being a bride once again.

657
00:23:53,839 --> 00:23:55,039
It feels like a dream.

658
00:23:55,920 --> 00:23:56,480
Not old, not old.

659
00:23:56,480 --> 00:23:58,119
My Yingzi will never be old.

660
00:23:58,119 --> 00:23:59,119
Oh, stop it.

661
00:24:00,880 --> 00:24:01,599
Little Cai.

662
00:24:02,279 --> 00:24:04,559
You must come back to our Evergreen Residence often.

663
00:24:04,799 --> 00:24:06,839
Come back often to see us all.

664
00:24:07,200 --> 00:24:08,240
Of course.

665
00:24:08,319 --> 00:24:09,400
That's my maiden home.

666
00:24:09,640 --> 00:24:10,519
The day after tomorrow...

667
00:24:10,559 --> 00:24:12,359
I'll take Old Cao back for the homecoming.

668
00:24:12,480 --> 00:24:14,160
Good.

669
00:24:16,279 --> 00:24:16,940
Hurry, hurry!

670
00:24:18,299 --> 00:24:19,240
Auntie Cai, don't worry.

671
00:24:23,180 --> 00:24:23,740
What's wrong?

672
00:24:24,460 --> 00:24:25,500
What happened?

673
00:24:26,460 --> 00:24:28,180
Grandpa Cao had a sudden heart attack.

674
00:24:28,980 --> 00:24:30,059
How did that happen?

675
00:24:30,180 --> 00:24:31,339
On the wedding night...

676
00:24:31,339 --> 00:24:32,660
Maybe he got too excited.

677
00:24:33,019 --> 00:24:34,779
Exactly, his old heart couldn't take it.

678
00:24:34,779 --> 00:24:35,579
Yeah.

679
00:24:35,779 --> 00:24:36,940
Could it be that just now...

680
00:24:36,940 --> 00:24:38,660
It was the wine you toasted Elder Cao with?

681
00:24:38,980 --> 00:24:40,220
How can you say that, child?

682
00:24:40,500 --> 00:24:42,180
I was the one who got myself drunk just now.

683
00:24:42,259 --> 00:24:43,579
Old Cao didn't drink a drop.

684
00:24:43,700 --> 00:24:44,380
No...

685
00:24:44,500 --> 00:24:46,740
What if something bad happens to Elder Cao?

686
00:24:46,819 --> 00:24:48,819
Little Cai's house hasn't been transferred yet, right?

687
00:24:48,980 --> 00:24:49,940
That's right.
